# 1. CLOUD VS ON-PREMISES
# ================================================================

ON-PREMISES:
- Servers in customer premises
- Buy hardware, cables, setup network
- Need system/network administrators
- Hardware outdated in 4-5 years
- Continuous patching/upgrading
- High cost + lots of planning

CLOUD (AWS/Azure/GCP):
- Data centers maintained by provider
- Pay only what you use (like electricity bill)
- No initial investment
- 2 minutes setup time
- Auto-scaling
- No maintenance headache
- 90% cost reduction
- 10x faster than on-premises

BILLING EXAMPLE:
- Use cluster = get bill
- Pause cluster = no bill
- Even $1 for 6 hours usage

